The North- East Development Commission (NEDC), has distributed eight truckload of relief materials to victims of Boko Haram attack in Garkida. Chairman of the commission Maj. Gen Paul Tarfa (rtd), who led the exercise Monday, assured the victims of quality and better structure in the rebuilding of structure damaged by the insurgents. Items distributed are 3000 bags of rice, 3000 blankets, 2000 mats, 2,520 bags of beans, 200 cartoons of maggi cubes, 100 bags of salt, 2000 cartoons of spaghetti and macaroni, 500 bags of maize flour, 3000 gallons of vegetable oil, 2000 pieces of wrapper and 500 cartoons of tomato paste. Tarfa said President Buhari is very much concerned about the attack, which prompt the intervention to enable the victims settle back to their houses. He reiterated government vigor to eliminating the insurgency completely and lauding the resilience of the victims. “The rebuilding is going to be blessing in the disguise through provision of quality job.” He admitted that, only few elements from the degraded insurgents are still carrying soft targets attacks. “Government is going to rise up to their challenges” Tarfa assured. Elisha Tumba, Commissioner Rehabilitation, Reconstruction and Reintegration, Adamawa state, who represented Governor Ahmadu Fintiri, in his remarks said, that the state government is in synergy with military authority for deployment of more personnel to the area. Gideon Gana, chairman vigilante of the area, expressed shock over the sophisticated weapons and tactics applied by the attackers. The insurgents had attacked Garkida and Biji-biji village killing two soldiers, burnt places of worship, and looted shop. The delegation inspected the divisional police headquarters, EYN church which was completely razed down and General Hospital Garkida where drugs were looted by the insurgents. 